 21     statute (Indiana Code 22-3-3-5.2). Please provide me with the following:
 22     
 23          1. An explanation of benefits.
 24          2. The name of the billing review service used.
 25          3. The dollar amount of the reduction.
 26          4. The statutory amount allowed for each item or service.
 27          5. In the case of a CPT code change, the basis upon which the change
 28             was made.
 29      
 30     Keep in mind, according to statute, billing review standards must be
 31     revised for prospective future payments.  The data used to perform the
 32     analysis and revision of the billing review standards may not be more
 33     than two years old and must be periodically updated by a representative
 34     inflationary or deflationary factor.

 34     assume the debt is valid. If you notify this office in writing within 30
 35     days of receiving this notice that you dispute the validity of this debt
 36     or any portion thereof, this office will obtain verification of the debt
 37     or obtain a copy of a judgment and mail you a copy of such judgment or
 38     verification. If you so request this office in writing within 30 days of
 39     receiving this notice, we will provide you with the name and address of
 40     the original creditor, if different from the current creditor.
 41     
 42     A consumer has the right to request in writing that a debt collector or
 43     collection agency cease further communication with the consumer. A
 44     written request to cease communication will not prohibit the debt
 45     collector or collection agency from taking any other action authorized by
 46     law to collect the debt. FOR INFORMATION ABOUT THE COLORADO FAIR DEBT
 47     COLLECTION PRACTICES ACT, SEE WWW.COLORADOATTORNEYGENERAL.GOV/CA.

 36     The state Rosenthal Fair Debt Collection Practices Act and the federal
 37     Fair Debt Collection Practices Act require that, except under unusual
 38     circumstances, collectors may not contact you before 8a.m. or after 9p.m.
 39     They may not harass you by using threats of violence or arrest or by
 40     using obscene language. Collectors may not use false or misleading
 41     statement or call you at work if they know or have reason to know that
 42     you may not receive personal calls at work. For the most part, collectors
 43     may not tell another person, other than your attorney or spouse, about
 44     your debt. Collectors may contact another person to confirm your location
 45     or enforce a judgment. For more information about debt collection
 46     activities, you may contact the Federal Trade Commission at
 47     1.877.FTC.HELP or www.ftc.gov. Nonprofit credit counseling services may
 48     be available in the area.

 36     The state Rosenthal Fair Debt Collection Practices Act and the federal
 37     Fair Debt Collection Practices Act require that, except under unusual
 38     circumstances, collectors may not contact you before 8a.m. or after 9p.m.
 39     They may not harass you by using threats of violence or arrest or by
 40     using obscene language. Collectors may not use false or misleading
 41     statement or call you at work if they know or have reason to know that
 42     you may not receive personal calls at work. For the most part, collectors
 43     may not tell another person, other than your attorney or spouse, about
 44     your debt. Collectors may contact another person to confirm your location
 45     or enforce a judgment. For more information about debt collection
 46     activities, you may contact the Federal Trade Commission at
 47     1.877.FTC.HELP or www.ftc.gov. Nonprofit credit counseling services may

 1      October 27, 2016                          50 Days Left in Open Enrollment
 2      
 3      
 4      Dear Customer,
 5      
 6      As a valued customer and patient of Community Health Network, we are
 7      grateful that we have been able to serve you and your family with quality
 8      health care.
 9      
 10     The cost of providing quality care continues to increase and Community
 11     Health Network encourages everyone to get the health care they need. In
 12     some instances we realize finding affordable coverage can be challenging
 13     and we have partnered with The WellFund in developing a new program that
 14     may be able to assist you in finding affordable coverage. Insurance
 15     coverage is now becoming more possible than ever before.
 16     
 17     With the Affordable Care Act now in place, the federal government has
 18     begun offering those without health insurance several options through the
 19     Health Insurance Marketplace. The Marketplace can provide coverage for
 20     you and your family. In addition to helping our patients with Marketplace
 21     insurance, The WellFunds Patient Advocates can assist with the
 22     application process for the government programs such as Medicaid and
 23     Social Security benefits. Enrollment can happen online, on the phone, or
 24     in person.
 25     
 26     For more information, please visit eCommunity.com/enroll. You can also
 27     call 855.365.9300 weekdays from 8:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. for assistance
 28     with enrollment. In order to have Marketplace insurance starting January
 29     1, 2017 and avoid possible tax penalties, you must enroll by December 15,
 30     2016.
 31     
 32     Once again, thank you for being a valued customer.

 3      Dear Customer,
 4      
 5      As a valued customer and patient of University of Tennessee Medical
 6      Center (UTMC), we are grateful that we have been able to serve you and
 7      your family with quality health care.
 8      
 9      The cost of providing quality care continues to increase and UTMC
 10     encourages everyone to get the healthcare they need. In some instances,
 11     we realize finding affordable coverage can be challenging and that is why
 12     we are partnering with The WellFund, who would like to work with you to
 13     determine if there is a program that meets your needs.
 14     
 15     With the Affordable Care Act now in place, the federal government has
 16     begun offering the uninsured several options through the Health Insurance
 17     Marketplace. The Marketplace can provide coverage for you and your family
 18     In addition to helping our patients with Marketplace insurance, our
 19     Patient Advocates can assist with the application process for government
 20     programs such as TennCare and Social Security benefits. Enrollment can
 21     happen online, on the phone, or in person.
 22     
 23     For more information, please call 855.365.9300 weekdays from 8:00 a.m. to
 24     5:00 p.m. EST for assistance with enrollment. Enrollment for Marketplace
 25     insurance starts November 1, 2016 for 2017 benefits.

 4      Dear Customer,
 5      
 6      As a valued customer and patient of University of Tennessee Medical
 7      Center (UTMC), we are grateful that we have been able to serve you and
 8      your family with quality health care.
 9      
 10     The cost of providing quality care continues to increase and UTMC
 11     encourages everyone to get the healthcare they need. In some instances,
 12     we realize finding affordable coverage can be challenging and that is why
 13     we are partnering with The WellFund, who would like to work with you to
 14     determine if there is a program that meets your needs.
 15     
 16     With the Affordable Car Act in place, the federal government has begun
 17     offering the uninsured several options through the Health Insurance
 18     Marketplace. The Marketplace can provide coverage for you and your family
 19     In addition to helping our patient's with Marketplace Insurance, our
 20     Patient Advocates can assist with the application process for government
 21     programs such as TennCare and Social Security benefits. Enrollment can
 22     happen online, on the phone, or in person.
 23     
 24     For more information, please call 865.213.1768 weekdays from 8:00 a.m. to
 25     5:00 p.m. EST for assistance with enrollment. Enrollment for Marketplace
 26     insurance stats November 1, 2018 for 2019 benefits.

 27      
 28     The state Rosenthal Fair Debt Collection Practices Act and the federal
 29     Fair Debt Collection Practices Act require that, except under unusual
 30     circumstances, collectors may not contact you before 8a.m. or after 9p.m.
 31     They may not harass you by using threats of violence or arrest or by
 32     using obscene language. Collectors may not use false or misleading
 33     statemets or call you at work if they know or have reason to know that
 34     you may not receive personal calls at work. For the most part, collectors
 35     may not tell another person, other than your attorney or spouse, about
 36     your debt. Collectors may contact another person to confirm your location
 37     or enforce a judgment. For more information about debt collection
 38     activities, you may contact the Federal Trade Commission at
 39     1.877.FTC.HELP or www.ftc.gov. Nonprofit credit counseling services may
 40     be available in the area.

 17     `HARRO`|||<EXIT>|<X>||X|
 18     3.7.2 ; Maintain Reports (3,7,2)|

 28     The state Rosenthal Fair Debt Collection Practices Act and the federal
 29     Fair Debt Collection Practices Act require that, except under unusual
 30     circumstances, collectors may not contact you before 8a.m. or after 9p.m.
 31     They may not harass you by using threats of violence or arrest or by
 32     using obscene language. Collectors may not use false or misleading
 33     statemets or call you at work if they know or have reason to know that
 34     you may not receive personal calls at work. For the most part, collectors
 35     may not tell another person, other than your attorney or spouse, about
 36     your debt. Collectors may contact another person to confirm your location
 37     or enforce a judgment. For more information about debt collection
 38     activities, you may contact the Federal Trade Commission at
 39     1.877.FTC.HELP or www.ftc.gov. Nonprofit credit counseling services may
 40     be available in the area.

 18     Dear <<DBRFIRST>> <<DBRLAST>>:
 19     
 20     We represent the above-named creditor. We have previously sent you a
 21     letter notifying you of this account and of your rights under the Fair
 22     Debt Collection Practices Act. To date, we have not had a resolution on
 23     this account.
 24      
 25     In order to resolve this matter, please call a MED-1 Solutions
 26     representative at 888.323.0811.
 27      
 28     The state Rosenthal Fair Debt Collection Practices Act and the federal
 29     Fair Debt Collection Practices Act require that, except under unusual
 30     circumstances, collectors may not contact you before 8a.m. or after 9p.m.
 31     They may not harass you by using threats of violence or arrest or by
 32     using obscene language. Collectors may not use false or misleading
 33     statemets or call you at work if they know or have reason to know that
 34     you may not receive personal calls at work. For the most part, collectors
 35     may not tell another person, other than your attorney or spouse, about
 36     your debt. Collectors may contact another person to confirm your location
 37     or enforce a judgment. For more information about debt collection
 38     activities, you may contact the Federal Trade Commission at
 39     1.877.FTC.HELP or www.ftc.gov. Nonprofit credit counseling services may
 40     be available in the area.
 41      
 42      
 43     Sincerely,
 44      
 45      
 46     MED-1 Solutions, LLC

 27      
 28     The state Rosenthal Fair Debt Collection Practices Act and the federal
 29     Fair Debt Collection Practices Act require that, except under unusual
 30     circumstances, collectors may not contact you before 8a.m. or after 9p.m.
 31     They may not harass you by using threats of violence or arrest or by
 32     using obscene language. Collectors may not use false or misleading
 33     statemets or call you at work if they know or have reason to know that
 34     you may not receive personal calls at work. For the most part, collectors
 35     may not tell another person, other than your attorney or spouse, about
 36     your debt. Collectors may contact another person to confirm your location
 37     or enforce a judgment. For more information about debt collection
 38     activities, you may contact the Federal Trade Commission at
 39     1.877.FTC.HELP or www.ftc.gov. Nonprofit credit counseling services may
 40     be available in the area.
